    "z05_sound": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div id=\"z05-twincore\" class=\"z05-feature-shell\"><section class=\"z05-section dark z05-twincore-section\"><div class=\"z05-wrap z05-grid-2\"><div><p class=\"z05-kicker\">TwinCore</p><h2>Same monitor, two listening moods</h2><div class=\"z05-definition\" role=\"note\"><span class=\"z05-definition-term\">TwinCore crossover:</span><p>A physical two-position crossover switch that changes how the dynamic woofer and balanced-armature paths are loaded, so Blue and Red shift the whole voicing rather than adding a simple bass boost.</p></div><p>Inside Z05 AuAg, TwinCore routes the monitor through two crossover voicings. The switch changes the electrical load seen by the low-frequency and high-frequency paths, shifting how much body the dynamic driver carries and how far the armatures step forward.</p><p>That is why the change is broad: bass pressure, vocal edge, cymbal air, and center image all move together. Many IEM switches behave like small trim controls; TwinCore feels closer to choosing between two crossover paths inside the same shell.</p><div class=\"z05-actions\"><a class=\"z05-btn\" href=\"/cart/add?id={{ product.selected_or_first_available_variant.id }}&quantity=1\">Buy Z05 AuAg</a></div></div><div class=\"z05-twincore-panel\"><img src=\"{{ 'z05-auag-twincore-switch-closeup.jpg' | asset_img_url: '1200x' }}\" alt=\"Z05 AuAg TwinCore switch with blue and red position markers\" loading=\"lazy\"><div class=\"z05-mechanism-grid\" aria-label=\"How TwinCore changes the crossover path\"><article><span>01</span><b>Switch position</b><p>The physical toggle selects Blue or Red without tools, apps, or recessed slots.</p></article><article><span>02</span><b>Crossover loading</b><p>The low-frequency and high-frequency paths see different loading, changing the driver handoff.</p></article><article><span>03</span><b>Driver balance</b><p>The dynamic woofer and armatures shift together, so the whole response changes as one voicing.</p></article></div><div class=\"z05-mode-grid\"><article><span>Blue Mode</span><h3>Weight / Flow</h3><p>A fuller low end, calmer upper harmonics, and a center image that feels easier to sit with for long albums.</p></article><article><span>Red Mode</span><h3>Focus / Spark</h3><p>Tighter bass outlines, more forward clarity, and extra cymbal air when you want the mix to open up.</p></article></div></div></div></section></div>",
