    "z05_tuned_by_kevin": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"z05-feature-shell\"><section id=\"z05-tuned-by-kevin\" class=\"z05-section dark z05-tuned-by-kevin\"><script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n{\n  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n  \"@graph\": [\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Person\",\n      \"@id\": \"https://www.aaw.me/#kevin-wang\",\n      \"name\": \"Kevin Wang\",\n      \"jobTitle\": \"Founder & Tuning Engineer\",\n      \"description\": \"Founder and tuning engineer of Advanced AcousticWerkes, involved in the acoustic design and tuning of AAW in-ear monitors.\",\n      \"knowsAbout\": [\"in-ear monitor tuning\",\"hybrid IEM design\",\"balanced armature drivers\",\"dynamic driver integration\",\"custom in-ear monitors\",\"universal in-ear monitors\"],\n      \"worksFor\": {\n        \"@id\": \"https://www.aaw.me/#organization\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"CreativeWork\",\n      \"@id\": {{ canonical_url | append: \"#z05-auag-design\" | json }},\n      \"name\": \"Z05 AuAg tuning and design journey by Kevin Wang\",\n      \"creator\": {\n        \"@id\": \"https://www.aaw.me/#kevin-wang\"\n      },\n      \"about\": {\n        \"@id\": {{ canonical_url | append: \"#product\" | json }}\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n</script><div class=\"z05-wrap z05-tuned-grid\"><div class=\"z05-tuned-heading\"><p class=\"z05-kicker\">Design Journey</p><h2>Tuned by Founder</h2><p class=\"z05-tuned-slogan\">Those who listen will find the way.</p></div><div class=\"z05-tuned-copy\"><p>The Z05 AuAg project began with a simple brief: make a universal AAW monitor that people would keep reaching for after the first demo. Kevin Wang approached it less as a smaller flagship and more as a daily companion: compact in the ear, quick to connect, and ready for the next album before the listener starts thinking about changing gear.</p><p>Early prototypes moved in different directions. Some sounded too polite, some too sharpened, and some asked the listener to adapt instead of letting the earphone follow the session. The design settled when the physical switch became part of the listening ritual: one position for sinking into the record, one for bringing the mix closer.</p><p>That path shaped the launch edition. AuAg gives the first pair a sense of ceremony with gold and silver hand finishing, but the design brief stays practical: a monitor that travels easily, changes mood without changing cables or sources, and still feels considered after the novelty fades.</p><blockquote><p>“I wanted Z05 AuAg to feel like the pair you leave on the desk because you know it will work with the next album. The switch is there because listening is not fixed; some nights need weight, some tracks need edges. The design had to respect that without making the product feel complicated.”</p><div class=\"z05-kevin-signature z05-kevin-signature-image\" aria-label=\"Kevin Wang signature\" role=\"img\"><img src=\"{{ 'kevin-wang-signature-gold.png' | asset_img_url: '958x' }}\" alt=\"Kevin Wang signature\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"958\" height=\"382\"><span>Kevin Wang</span></div><cite>Kevin Wang<br><span>Founder & Tuning Engineer, Advanced AcousticWerkes</span></cite></blockquote></div></div></section></div>",
