    "z05_faq": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n{\n  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n  \"@type\": \"FAQPage\",\n  \"mainEntity\": [\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What does AuAg mean?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Au is gold, Ag is silver. On this launch edition, the identity is split left and right with gold and silver accents over the hand-finished shell work, while forged-carbon faceplates carry the visual identity.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Is this only a cosmetic edition?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"No. The finish gets attention first, but the reason to stay is the Z05 platform: dynamic bass, balanced armature clarity, Bass-Flow pressure control, and TwinCore voicing.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What does the TwinCore switch change?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"TwinCore is a physical two-position acoustic voicing switch on each earpiece. It toggles between Blue mode for warmer, fuller bass and Red mode for brighter, more detailed treble with tighter bass outlines and more cymbal air.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What is the difference between Blue mode and Red mode?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Blue mode gives Z05 AuAg a fuller low end, calmer upper harmonics, and an easier long-session center image. Red mode tightens bass outlines, brings clarity forward, and adds cymbal air when you want the mix to open up.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Is Z05 AuAg suitable for live performers or only casual listening?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Z05 AuAg can serve both use cases. It is a compact universal hybrid IEM with dynamic-driver weight, balanced-armature clarity, and repeatable isolation from LiquidMorph ear tips. Live performance suitability still depends on fit, isolation needs, and personal monitoring level.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Is Z05 AuAg easy to drive from a phone dongle?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Yes. Z05 AuAg is intended to work across phone dongles, DAPs, compact DAC/amps, and desktop sources. A low-output-impedance source below 1 Ohm and low or medium gain are recommended for best noise control.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Is Z05 AuAg suitable for small ears?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Z05 AuAg uses a compact universal shell rather than a custom mold. The smaller body and LiquidMorph ear tips are designed to help more listeners get a stable seal, but fit still depends on individual ear shape and tip size.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What is included in the box?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"The kit includes the Z05 AuAg monitors, a 2-pin detachable cable, 3.5mm stereo, 4.4mm balanced, and USB Type-C terminations, a carrying case, and LiquidMorph ear tips.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Where can I demo AAW Z05 AuAg in Singapore?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"In Singapore, you can start with AAW Office, Zeppelin & Co., JABEN, or AV One. For demo, support, warranty, or dealer questions, contact AAW Singapore at sales@acousticwerkes.com or +65-8731-5476, or use the store locator for more listening points.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"How does Z05 AuAg compare with custom IEMs?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Z05 AuAg is a universal-fit IEM, so it does not require ear impressions or a custom shell. Custom IEMs can offer a personalized fit, while Z05 AuAg focuses on compact universal fit, fast source flexibility, included terminations, and the physical TwinCore voicing switch.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What warranty or support is available in Singapore?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"For Singapore demo, product support, warranty, or dealer questions, contact AAW Singapore at sales@acousticwerkes.com or +65-8731-5476.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Does Z05 AuAg come with a warranty?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Yes. Z05 AuAg includes a 1-year warranty covering manufacturing defects under normal use. For warranty support, contact AAW Singapore or the authorized dealer where you purchased it.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Can I buy Z05 AuAg outside Singapore?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Yes. Outside Singapore, AAW works with specialist audio stores and listening rooms across Hong Kong, Macau, Japan, China, South Korea, and Thailand. Use the store locator to find the closest authorized listening point or dealer.\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n</script><div class=\"z05-feature-shell\"><section class=\"z05-section\"><div class=\"z05-wrap z05-grid-2\"><div><p class=\"z05-kicker\">FAQ</p><h2>Frequently asked questions about Z05 AuAg</h2><p>A few notes before you hit play. The short version for anyone deciding whether this belongs in the daily rotation.</p></div><div class=\"z05-faq\"><details open><summary>What does AuAg mean?</summary><p>Au is gold, Ag is silver. On this launch edition, the identity is split left and right with gold and silver accents over the hand-finished shell work, while forged-carbon faceplates carry the visual identity.</p></details><details><summary>Is this only a cosmetic edition?</summary><p>No. The finish gets attention first, but the reason to stay is the Z05 platform: dynamic bass, balanced armature clarity, Bass-Flow pressure control, and TwinCore voicing.</p></details><details><summary>What does the TwinCore switch change?</summary><p>TwinCore is a physical two-position acoustic voicing switch on each earpiece. It toggles between Blue mode for warmer, fuller bass and Red mode for brighter, more detailed treble with tighter bass outlines and more cymbal air.</p></details><details><summary>What is the difference between Blue mode and Red mode?</summary><p>Blue mode gives Z05 AuAg a fuller low end, calmer upper harmonics, and an easier long-session center image. Red mode tightens bass outlines, brings clarity forward, and adds cymbal air when you want the mix to open up.</p></details><details><summary>Is Z05 AuAg suitable for live performers or only casual listening?</summary><p>Z05 AuAg can serve both use cases. It is a compact universal hybrid IEM with dynamic-driver weight, balanced-armature clarity, and repeatable isolation from LiquidMorph ear tips. Live performance suitability still depends on fit, isolation needs, and personal monitoring level.</p></details><details><summary>Is Z05 AuAg easy to drive from a phone dongle?</summary><p>Yes. Z05 AuAg is intended to work across phone dongles, DAPs, compact DAC/amps, and desktop sources. A low-output-impedance source below 1 Ohm and low or medium gain are recommended for best noise control.</p></details><details><summary>Is Z05 AuAg suitable for small ears?</summary><p>Z05 AuAg uses a compact universal shell rather than a custom mold. The smaller body and LiquidMorph ear tips are designed to help more listeners get a stable seal, but fit still depends on individual ear shape and tip size.</p></details><details><summary>What is included in the box?</summary><p>The kit includes the Z05 AuAg monitors, a 2-pin detachable cable, 3.5mm stereo, 4.4mm balanced, and USB Type-C terminations, a carrying case, and LiquidMorph ear tips.</p></details><details><summary>Where can I demo AAW Z05 AuAg in Singapore?</summary><p>In Singapore, you can start with AAW Office, Zeppelin & Co., JABEN, or AV One. For demo, support, warranty, or dealer questions, contact AAW Singapore at sales@acousticwerkes.com or +65-8731-5476, or use the store locator for more listening points.</p></details><details><summary>How does Z05 AuAg compare with custom IEMs?</summary><p>Z05 AuAg is a universal-fit IEM, so it does not require ear impressions or a custom shell. Custom IEMs can offer a personalized fit, while Z05 AuAg focuses on compact universal fit, fast source flexibility, included terminations, and the physical TwinCore voicing switch.</p></details><details><summary>Does Z05 AuAg come with a warranty?</summary><p>Yes. Z05 AuAg includes a 1-year warranty covering manufacturing defects under normal use. For warranty support, contact AAW Singapore or the authorized dealer where you purchased it.</p></details><details><summary>Can I buy Z05 AuAg outside Singapore?</summary><p>Yes. Outside Singapore, AAW works with specialist audio stores and listening rooms across Hong Kong, Macau, Japan, China, South Korea, and Thailand. Use the store locator to find the closest authorized listening point or dealer.</p></details><details><summary>What warranty or support is available in Singapore?</summary><p>For Singapore demo, product support, warranty, or dealer questions, contact AAW Singapore at sales@acousticwerkes.com or +65-8731-5476.</p></details></div></div></section><section class=\"z05-final\"><div class=\"z05-wrap z05-final-inner\"><h2>Choose the mood, keep the monitor</h2><p>Those who listen will find the way.</p><p>A launch-edition Z05 with real low-end body, armature detail, and a physical switch for the way your listening mood actually changes.</p><div class=\"z05-actions\"><a class=\"z05-btn\" href=\"/cart/add?id={{ product.selected_or_first_available_variant.id }}&quantity=1\">Buy Now</a></div></div></section></div>",
